<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[2086,2680,2578,3000]" lastBlockId="3.[1474,2679,3007,3473]" pageId="3" pageNumber="31">
According to mtDNA, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1922" box="[2419,2558,2731,2764]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nubrica">O. nubrica</taxonomicName>
belongs to subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Link" authorityYear="1795" box="[2283,2403,2771,2804]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Ochotona</taxonomicName>
. Taxonomic status of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1922" box="[2128,2264,2814,2843]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nubrica">O. nubrica</taxonomicName>
was unstable for a long time. Different authors placed it into 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Pallas" baseAuthorityYear="1769" box="[2552,2680,2853,2882]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusilla">O. pusilla</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[2129,2285,2892,2921]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thibetana">O. thibetana</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1922" box="[2303,2528,2892,2921]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nubrica">Ochotona nubrica</taxonomicName>
was elevated to full species status after morphological revision in 1992. Although its mtDNA variation is entirely within variation of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[2012,2171,3007,3040]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="curzoniae">O. curzoniae</taxonomicName>
, its nDNA genes confirm taxonomic singularity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1922" box="[1678,1818,3046,3079]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nubrica">O. nubrica</taxonomicName>
. It hybridize with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[2090,2254,3046,3079]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="31" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="curzoniae">O. curzoniae</taxonomicName>
, eliminating its own mtDNA. According to morphological study, it includes aliensis, lama, and lhasaensis. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
